IN the INTEREST OF: Z.V. II Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
V.W. (Mother) and Z.V. (Father), Appellants. WD 81631
(Consolidated with WD 81635) Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: October 16, 2018 Ryan F. Kaiser, Kansas City, MO, Attorney for Respondent. Laurie V. Snell, Kansas City, MO, Attorney for Appellant V.W. Dana M. Outlaw, Blue Springs, MO, Attorney for Appellant Z.V. Before Division Two: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, and Lisa White Hardwick and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

V.W. and Z.V. appeal from the Judgment of the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri, Family Court Division, terminating their parental rights. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
